text: “My home is in Heaven. I'm just traveling through this world.” - Billy Graham

It's been a great first year with historic tax relief, economic growth, and better services for our veterans. Today's vote was huge!
Our troops now have what they need to keep us safe and free, and our cotton farmers have what they need to keep us fed and clothed.

I am glad to know Senate Democrats have retreated from their ill-conceived and outrageous demand we shut down our government, disrupt our military, and halt funding for other important obligations over amnesty for people who entered our country illegally.
After eight long years of big government “Obamanomics” resulting in low wages, low job participation, and no economic growth, the American people will soon be getting a much deserved break.

The lack of management, oversight & accountability at the VA is astonishing, but in order to turn the VA around, we must be empowered with correct and timely data on the VA’s practices and performance.

I am thrilled the Senate was able to seize this historic opportunity to deliver tax relief for hard working families, simplify the tax code, make America competitive again, and grow our economy by keeping our jobs and companies from going overseas.

Happy Thanksgiving from our family to yours! My list of things to be thankful for is endless, but I want y’all to know that I thank God every day for the opportunity to serve our great country and represent the people of West Texas.
